<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910121-0041</DOCNO><DOCID>910121-0041.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Communications Satellite Corp.:   Loss for Quarter and Year   To Be Posted by Company</HL><DATE>01/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3</SO><CO>   CQ</CO><IN>COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)</IN><LP>   Communications Satellite Corp. said a restructuring of oneof its businesses will result in a charge of $3.60 to $4 ashare for its fourth quarter, and a loss for the quarter andfull year.   The pre-tax charge will be in the range of $90 million to$100 million.</LP><TEXT>   The Washington, D.C., communications company didn'testimate the size of the losses. In the year-earlier quarter,net income was $7.6 million, or 39 cents a share, on revenueof $100.4 million. For 1989, Comsat earned $62.5 million, or$3.35 a share, on revenue of $411.5 million.   Comsat said that the charge will result from therestructuring of its business to distribute televisionprogramming to hotels and that it would eliminate aboutone-third of the 200 jobs in that unit, called Comsat VideoEnterprises.</TEXT></DOC>